Joanna Lumley launches appeal to save Peter Pan windows
Joanna Lumley, the actress, has today launched a campaign to save the childhood playground of JM Barrie, asking his loyal readers to sponsor the very windows which inspired Peter Pan.
Joanna Lumley By Hannah Furness
7:00AM BST 23 Sep 2013
Follow Comments
Lumley, who is a patron of the Peter Pan Moat Brae Trust, said the “marvellous” campaign would ensure the real birthplace of the children’s story remained standing.
She has now appealed to readers to help save the “sacred” piece of history and keep the “magical place alive” for the next generation.
