Woman dragged by truck carrying dead bodies
A truck carrying the bodies of the victims of a massacre in Mexico has crushed a woman when it crashed into two cars and pushed them down a street. 1:36PM BST 02 Sep 2010
The truck, transporting 72 frozen corpses of migrants to a morgue, crashed and crushed 20-year-old Elba Gonzalezas between two cars, which were then dragged down a street.
Gonzalez is in a serious condition in hospital, suffering from a hemorrhage in one of her legs.
The bodies which the truck was carrying were found at a remote ranch near the US border and are believed to be victims of Mexico's increasingly bloody drug war.
